Piątki  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Nidzica, within Nidzica County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south-west of Nidzica and  south of the regional capital Olsztyn. It is located in Masuria.
The existence of the village is attested in 1412, when Mikołaj (Nicholas) of Piątki was mentioned.
